\sin x = x + O(x^3)
\begin{align}\frac{1}{\sin x} &= \frac{1}{x + O(x^3)} \\ &= \frac{1}{x} \left( \frac{1}{1 - O(x^2))} \right) \\ &= \frac{1}{x} \left(1 + O(x^2) \right) \\ &= \frac{1}{x} + O(x) \end{align}
